<p>Here are a few of the 100-ish feeds I follow. To see them all, visit <a href="https://web.cobb.land/weekly">The Good Web Weekly</a>.</p>

<div class="blogroll">
    <ul>
        {% for blog in collections.blog | sort(attribute='data.title') %}
            <li>
                {% if blog.data.icon === "yes" %}
                    <a class="link-icon" href="{{ blog.data.link }}">
                        <img class="icon-image" src="{{ blog.data.image }}" alt="{{ blog.data.title }}">
                    </a>
                {% else %}
                    <a class="link-icon" href="{{ blog.data.link }}">
                        <svg class="icon-svg" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" alt="{{ blog.data.title }}" height="31" width="88">
                            <rect class="icon-rect" width="88" height="31" fill="#{{ blog.data.color }}">
                            {% if blog.data.image !== "no" %}
                                <img class="icon-image" src="{{ blog.data.image }}" alt="{{ blog.data.title }}">
                            {% endif %}
                            <span class="icon-text">{{ blog.data.title }}</span>
                            <img class="icon-border" src="/images/button-outline-88x31.png" aria-hidden="true">
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                {% endif %}
            </li>
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</div>

<p class="note">Note that I use the term "blogroll" loosely here. Most websites linked above are blogs, but some may be digital gardens, wikis, portfolios, newsletters, et cetera. Also note that inclusion in this blogroll is not an endorsement.</p>

<p>If you'd like to link to me, feel free to use my badge. Please let me know if you do, so I can link to you (if you're cool).</p>

<a class="link-icon" href="https://cobb.land">
